Uninor Head Says Company Has Started Process to Raise INR82 Bln

-- B y   M e e r a   B h a t i a
-- 
2011-09-22T12:26:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/uninor-head-says-company-has-started-process-to-raise-inr82-bln.html
Telenor ASA (TEL) ’s India unit head said
today that the company has started a process to raise 82 billion
rupees.  “What has been decided by the board of Uninor is that we
want to raise 82 billion equity to finance the rest of the plan
and take care of some of the short-term borrowing that we
currently have,” Sigve Brekke, managing director of Uninor said
in an interview today. “There are no more obstables” to the
rights issue, said Brekke, who is not looking for other partners
for its India venture.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Meera Bhatia at 
 mbhatia2@bloomberg.net  